column2: Using a cryptographically weak pseudo-random number generator to generate a security-sensitive value may allow an attacker to predict what value will be generated.
column4: This uses a cryptographically insecure random number generated at [["Math.random()"|"relative:///VulnFinder-CodeQL-main/src/javascript-cwe/CWE-338/examples/InsecureRandomness.js:3:18:3:30"]] in a security context.
